<exercisegroup><introduction><p>For Problems 18<ndash/>21, <ol label="a">
	<li>Choose variables for the two unknown quantities in the problem.</li>
	<li>Write a system of equations to model the problem.</li>
	<li>Solve the system and answer the question.</li></ol></p></introduction>

<exercise number="18"><statement><p>A hamburger and a chocolate shake together contain 1030 calories. Two shakes and three hamburgers contain 2710 calories. How many calories are there in one hamburger and in one chocolate shake?</p></statement>
</exercise>

<exercise number="19"><statement><p>Darryl is in charge of buying furniture for a new restaurant. Chairs cost $175 and tables cost $250. Darryl's budget allows $11,400 for tables and chairs, and he plans to buy four chairs for each table.  How many of each can he buy?</p></statement>
<answer><p><ol label="a">
    <li><p>Number of chairs: <m>x</m>, number of tables: <m>y</m></p></li>
    <li><md><mrow>175x+250y=11,400</mrow>
            <mrow>x=4y</mrow></md></li>
    <li>He can buy 12 tables and 48 chairs.</li></ol></p></answer></exercise>

<exercise number="20"><statement><p>The perimeter of a rectangle is 42 meters, and its width is 13 meters less than its length. Find the dimensions of the rectangle.</p></statement></exercise>

<exercise number="21"><statement><p>Three pounds of bacon and 2 pounds of coffee costs $17.80. Two pounds of bacon and 5 pounds of coffee costs $32.40. How much do 1 pound of bacon and 1 pound of coffee cost?</p></statement>
<answer><p><ol label="a">
    <li><p>Cost of 1 lb of bacon: <m>x</m>, cost of 1 lb of coffee: <m>y</m></p></li>
    <li><md><mrow>3x+2y=17.80</mrow>
            <mrow>2x+5y=32.40</mrow></md></li>
    <li>One pound of bacon costs $2.20, and one pound of coffee costs $5.60. </li></ol></p></answer></exercise>
</exercisegroup>
 
